    <p>A min­i­mal kitchen de­sign falls flat when clunky small ap­pli­ances, like toast­ers and rice cook­ers, clut­ter up the space.</p>
    <p>When de­sign­ing your kitchen, des­ig­nate con­cealed stor­age that cam­ou­flages ap­pli­ances.</p>
    <p>Ar­clinea’s Mini Ap­pli­ance Con­tainer Unit (above) has a pull-out wood shelf to free up counter space, two elec­tric sock­ets and in­ter­nal light­ing, plus a mir­ror-fin­ish Stop­sol tem­pered glass door with a built-in grip. Avail­able at Unique Kitchen Fu­sion.</p>

